does your hair change during pregnancy i recently had a miscarriage about a month ago but my hair has always been extremely curly and now it's starting to turn straight i was wondering if this was from the pregnancy but shouldn't those hormones have stopped i haven't straightened my hair in forever because i live in humid weather i am so sorry for your loss hormones are funny things your body may have adapted to being pregnant and may just be takin a little while longer to adjust back to normal through out my pregnancy my hair was so straight smooth and silky and now it is straw like and fuzzy so hormones definately take part in your hair changing but im not too sure when things should get back to normal it can take a while but how long depends on your individual body i would consult a doctor to check your levels out and take it from there Pregnancy Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Prostate cancer Puberty Hair Miscarriage Guinea pig Oral contraceptive Menstrual cycle Obstetrics Prolactinoma Human skin color Leaf Folic acid Abortion debate Fertility awareness Breastfeeding Acne Human height Polycystic ovary syndrome Endometriosis Baldness Growth hormone treatment Gender role Nutrition Sexual differentiation Abortion Pregnancy test Homosexuality and transgender Dog Marilyn Monroe Turner syndrome Urinary incontinence Baldness treatments Diabetes mellitus Chemotherapy Childbirth Drag racing Protein Testosterone Graves-Basedow disease Haircut Spina bifida Aerial (dance move) Twin Friends Morning sickness Kender Human chorionic gonadotropin Cephalic disorder Osteoporosis Anabolic steroid Hearing impairment Shaggy dog story Progesterone Insulin Mattress Elephant Hypertension Coeliac disease Biology and sexual orientation Hypoglycemia Phoebe Halliwell Milton H. Erickson Inflation fetishism Drug test Equine conformation Premature birth Theory of conduct Psoriasis Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Glucocorticoid Intersexuality Intact dilation and extraction